@jiazhai As mentioned in the commit, I made this change to Long so I could implement the `clearOffloadThreshold` API call. This is done to make it be consistent with the `clearOffloadDeletionLag` call and is also required in order to differentiate between the case of no overridden value for the namespace and of having offloading disabled.

As an example, if I have a cluster wide namespace default of 12 hours but I want to disable offloading (by setting the value to -1) for a single namespace, then I can't use -1 also as the the sentinel value to see if the namespace has an overridden value as it is ambiguous.

There is another option here, which is to have `0` disable offloading and `-1`  be used as the default value, however, that still makes the API inconsistent with the other similar configuration option of `offloadDeletionLag`. It seems like there should be a consistent pattern for all of these configuration options and I am happy to do whatever fits that consistent pattern.

